outlook is for widening longevity gaps between the sexes. On the other hand, 
there was more good news, as the infant mortality rate decreased dramatically, 
falling to a record low. Also encouraging is the continued, if somewhat 
unsteady, long-term trend toward gradual narrowing of the white/non-white/black 
life expectancy differentials.

