world with dyslipidemia, hypertension and cigarette smoking leading a long list 
of risk factors. Recently, controversy arose from some critical articles 
expressing concern about the evaluation and interpretation of statistical data 
of epidemiologic studies. One study using covariance analysis reported an 
absence of the widely accepted negative association between coronary heart 
